+  // - does not split natural log (ln) into high / low parts
+  // - clamps exp(x) to 0 for x < -87.683113f and inf for x > 88.3762589f
+  // exp(x) = 2^n (exp(r))
+  // r = x - n*ln2, with n = round(x/ln2)
+  // exp(r) ~ poly(r) = 1 + r + r^2 * (c3 + c2 * r)
+  // n = round(x / ln2), r = x - n*ln2
